==English==

===Etymology===
Recorded since 1340, from {{etyl|fro}} [[incorrigible]] (1334), or directly from {{etyl|la}} [[incorrigibilis]] "not to be corrected", from [[in-]] "not" + [[corrigere]] "to correct" + [[-ibilis]] '-able' 

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Impossible to [[correct]] or set [[aright]]. 
# Incurably depravd, not reformable.
# Impervious to correction by punishment or pain
# [[unmanageable]]
# Determined, [[unalterable]], hence impossible to improve upon
#:''The laws of nature and mathematics are '''incorrigible'''
# {{Archaic}} [[incurable]]

====Usage notes====
* {{sense|Impossible to correct or set aright}} {{term|incorrigible|Incorrigible}} is a complex term that has antithetical denotations.  In certain contexts, it may be synonymous with {{term|impeccable}}.

